        "created_at": "2025-03-14T17:38:16.237Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I’ve been using Signal Desktop as my primary messaging tool for ages. I’d originally register my accounts directly from Signal Desktop itself (i.e. primary, standalone) by compiling the software from source and added features for direct registration through the desktop client. In other words, there has never been any other device, the SIM cards using to register the accounts are also long gone. Barely relevant, but my personal setup includes separate AppVMs in Qubes OS for each Signal account.</p>\n<p>Now on a travel with a small laptop, I noticed that one of my accounts has stopped delivering messages since yesterday, strangely enough except for the very last message. Could this be related to any updates? I keep my clients updated, running updates every few days, but never more than a week apart. This is definitely unusual behaviour. Could the database have become corrupted?</p>",
