        "created_at": "2025-03-16T16:32:29.795Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Downgrading to 7.45.1 resolved the issue, for whatever reason. I’m unsure of what to do next and would prefer not to be stuck on an old version indefinitely.</p>\n<p>The problem might also be network related. The AppVM in question which runs Signal is based on the Whonix Workstation template. Perhaps it’s something to do with the lack of UDP support or other restrictions?</p>\n<p>As for the log, I’m extremely cautious with those accounts and prefer not to tamper with what’s essential for my communication with the outside world. In the event that switching back and forth between the versions ultimately causes it to break altogether, I’m in deep trouble.</p>",
