        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"pitrinetro\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"67686\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/pitrinetro/48/43890_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> pitrinetro:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>the SIM cards using to register the accounts are also long gone</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>You should consider changing the number before it is too late. If you don’t want to use a mobile phone, look at <a href=\"https://github.com/AsamK/signal-cli\">Signal-CLI</a> or an Android emulator if your changes to the Signal-Desktop don’t permit changing your number. Using one of the suggestions above would also let you use the official Signal-Desktop client as a linked device.</p>",
