        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/cuehd/{size}/42510_2.png",
        "created_at": "2025-03-25T13:25:08.085Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"pitrinetro\" data-post=\"6\" data-topic=\"67686\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/pitrinetro/48/43890_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> pitrinetro:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>It is the official client that I use though.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>I didn’t mean to imply that you were using a nonofficial client now. I meant that you could continue to use the official client but as a linked device instead of a primary device.</p>\n<p>My suggestion for Signal-CLI or an Android emulator was only for the purpose of changing your number to a SIM that you control not for ongoing messaging.</p>",
