      {
        "id": 264326,
        "name": "pitrinetro",
        "username": "pitrinetro",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/pitrinetro/{size}/43890_2.png",
        "created_at": "2025-03-26T09:05:15.969Z",
        "cooked": "<p>There won’t be a SIM under my control for more than a couple of months anyway. To control a SIM means to research, track the terms of service, and manage billing for something I have no long term use for. Possibly even having to own, manage, update, a mobile device long term.</p>\n<p>I’ve heard of services that provide virtual phone numbers via a website, linked to a user account and paid for in cryptocurrencies, but even here I think the sustainability is uncertain.</p>\n<p>Also, if nothing is ever changed or done incorrectly on my part, and I log in nearly every day for years, I don’t see why a service would need me to verify my identity under the threat of cutting me off.</p>\n<p>I recognise though that there is a genuine risk of someone else registering an account with the recycled number that was used for mine. However, in real world situations, especially with numbers from country codes where Signal isn’t widely used, I believe this is very unlikely to occur. At least, it hasn’t happened to any of the many accounts since around 2017. It was always changes in Signal itself, or maybe the fact that they would at times simply wipe such accounts off, that would put them to an end.</p>",
