        "username": "dreieck",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/dreieck/{size}/49457_2.png",
        "created_at": "2025-03-27T16:23:11.691Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"pitrinetro\" data-post=\"8\" data-topic=\"67686\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/pitrinetro/48/43890_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> pitrinetro:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p><em>I recognise though that there is a genuine risk of someone else registering an account with the recycled number that was used for mine.</em></p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>This actually happened for an old Telegram account of mine.</p>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"pitrinetro\" data-post=\"8\" data-topic=\"67686\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/pitrinetro/48/43890_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> pitrinetro:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p><em>Also, if nothing is ever changed or done incorrectly on my part, and I log in nearly every day for years, I don’t see why a service would need me to verify my identity under the threat of cutting me off.</em></p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>This is something I experiences Signal was doing frequently on me in the past (not since about one year now). So, for a service which actually requires a phone number to receive SMS, to not have the fear that out of a sudden you cannot use it anymore it makes sense to keep access to the phone number ans SMS on that number.<br>\nI needed it for Signal already. (And I use an anonymous prepaid SIM for this, which I only use for this service.)</p>",
