        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"pitrinetro\" data-post=\"6\" data-topic=\"67686\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/pitrinetro/48/43890_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> pitrinetro:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>the last time I checked, Android emulators were absolutely dreadful.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Yeah, they are pretty bad. The least awful one I’ve found is the one baked into Google’s Android Studio.</p>\n<p>My biggest complaint is there is no way to upgrade the OS in place. No security updates. No major version updates. Play store updates do work if you choose an image with play store support.</p>\n<p>When a new OS is released you can create a new VM with the new OS release, but then you have to set up all your apps again. It’s sort of like getting a new phone but without any transfer capabilities.</p>",
